1
00:00:05,801 --> 00:00:07,531
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,601 --> 00:00:09,201
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,471 --> 00:00:12,031
(Episode 44)

4
00:00:12,101 --> 00:00:15,101
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

5
00:00:15,541 --> 00:00:18,541
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

6
00:00:33,521 --> 00:00:35,161
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

7
00:00:42,931 --> 00:00:44,931
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

8
00:00:53,811 --> 00:00:57,211
Do you happen to know
where Jo Mi Hyang might be?

9
00:00:58,711 --> 00:01:00,121
I don't know.

10
00:01:04,751 --> 00:01:07,591
But I know,

11
00:01:08,521 --> 00:01:11,061
how we can catch Jo Mi Hyang.

12
00:01:12,731 --> 00:01:16,031
Jo Mi Hyang can't live without me.

13
00:01:17,401 --> 00:01:21,641
She can't do anything on her own
and has always relied solely on me.

14
00:01:22,101 --> 00:01:23,871
So...

15
00:01:24,611 --> 00:01:26,381
how about you use me as bait?

16
00:01:26,911 --> 00:01:29,251
Father, what are you talking about?

17
00:01:29,411 --> 00:01:33,551
Wait, sir. Are you saying you'll
lure out Jo Mi Hyang yourself?

18
00:01:34,181 --> 00:01:38,921
- That's right.
- What? No, Father. Absolutely not.

19
00:01:38,991 --> 00:01:42,461
He's right, sir. We don't
know what Jo Mi Hyang might do.

20
00:01:42,591 --> 00:01:45,961
We can't leave you exposed
like that. It's too dangerous.

21
00:01:46,101 --> 00:01:49,971
Well, I can't stay
in hiding forever.

22
00:01:50,671 --> 00:01:53,641
I understand how you feel.

23
00:01:53,941 --> 00:01:57,371
But please, trust us
and wait a little longer.

24
00:01:57,441 --> 00:01:59,181
He's right, Father.

25
00:02:13,221 --> 00:02:14,821
(Onjeong Traditional Market)

26
00:02:20,801 --> 00:02:22,001
What should I do?

27
00:02:23,331 --> 00:02:24,401
No.

28
00:02:25,471 --> 00:02:28,171
There's no way he abandoned me.

29
00:02:30,971 --> 00:02:32,881
Those people took him.

30
00:02:33,641 --> 00:02:36,011
They took him away from me.

31
00:02:42,891 --> 00:02:46,021
What do you mean? Bait?

32
00:02:46,591 --> 00:02:49,431
Father, that's too dangerous.

33
00:02:49,761 --> 00:02:50,861
Absolutely not.

34
00:02:50,861 --> 00:02:54,101
Father, don't even think about it.
Understand?

35
00:02:54,331 --> 00:02:58,301
Father, a person with a twisted obsession
like Jo Mi Hyang...

36
00:02:58,371 --> 00:03:00,641
is capable of anything.

37
00:03:00,771 --> 00:03:04,641
It's because my family is
suffering so much because of me.

38
00:03:04,711 --> 00:03:09,411
I know. But you doing this
will only make it harder on us.

39
00:03:09,411 --> 00:03:10,481
She's right.

40
00:03:10,481 --> 00:03:14,221
- Just focus on your recovery, okay?
- Father.

41
00:03:18,691 --> 00:03:20,691
Just hold it steady
and shine the light properly, okay?

42
00:03:20,691 --> 00:03:22,991
Gosh, seriously.

43
00:03:28,001 --> 00:03:29,201
There.

44
00:03:30,931 --> 00:03:33,001
What? What is it?

45
00:03:40,611 --> 00:03:42,211
- Oh my.
- Gosh, my back.

46
00:03:49,391 --> 00:03:51,421
- Father, I think this is it.
- Yes.

47
00:03:52,151 --> 00:03:53,721
- Oh my.
- Oh my.

48
00:03:54,121 --> 00:03:55,691
- Oh my.
- Oh my.

49
00:04:02,501 --> 00:04:04,271
What's going on here?

50
00:04:04,531 --> 00:04:08,841
You two said you had no feelings
for each other. So what's this?

51
00:04:08,901 --> 00:04:11,371
Then what are you two doing here?

52
00:04:11,441 --> 00:04:15,981
Oh, we were just passing by
and wondered if you were here.

53
00:04:16,251 --> 00:04:18,911
The light went out,
so we were changing the bulb.

54
00:04:19,421 --> 00:04:20,421
Are you sure?

55
00:04:23,191 --> 00:04:24,991
That brat...

56
00:04:25,091 --> 00:04:29,391
If you have eyes, take a look.
Does this look romantic to you?

57
00:04:29,461 --> 00:04:31,231
Then you should've
kept your balance.

58
00:04:31,291 --> 00:04:33,101
Why'd you cause this
misunderstanding?

59
00:04:33,101 --> 00:04:36,401
Seriously? You should've held
the ladder steady.

60
00:04:36,471 --> 00:04:38,601
You shouldn't have
fallen on me, Director Yang.

61
00:04:38,671 --> 00:04:41,101
Then you should've moved.
Why did you hug me?

62
00:04:41,171 --> 00:04:43,411
Is this a hug? It was a reflex.
I just caught you.

63
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:47,181
- Gosh, what a horrible thought.
- What? Horrible?

64
00:04:47,241 --> 00:04:49,311
Right. Just touching
you gives me the creeps.

65
00:04:49,381 --> 00:04:50,911
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.

66
00:04:54,521 --> 00:04:57,151
- Let's go, Se Ri.
- Yes, Father.

67
00:05:13,301 --> 00:05:15,701
Did they really used to date?

68
00:05:16,041 --> 00:05:19,941
I'm not sure.
I'm a bit confused myself, Father.

69
00:05:21,911 --> 00:05:23,881
They seemed pretty hostile.

70
00:05:24,451 --> 00:05:25,451
I know.

71
00:05:25,851 --> 00:05:27,751
Oh, Father.
I guess we don't have to worry...

72
00:05:27,821 --> 00:05:29,851
about becoming
double in-laws anymore, right?

73
00:05:29,921 --> 00:05:32,321
Of course not. That can't happen.

74
00:05:32,621 --> 00:05:33,791
That's such a relief.

75
00:05:38,791 --> 00:05:42,971
They could've made a sound.
Why sneak around and peek?

76
00:05:43,031 --> 00:05:45,231
They said they were just passing by.

77
00:05:45,471 --> 00:05:49,411
Passing by or not, why do they
keep coming to my workplace?

78
00:05:49,471 --> 00:05:52,071
I really hate being
misunderstood like this.

79
00:05:52,711 --> 00:05:56,251
I'll tell them not to even
pass by this area anymore.

80
00:05:56,581 --> 00:05:59,351
- Happy now?
- Am I making a fuss for no reason?

81
00:05:59,721 --> 00:06:02,721
Your mother keeps assuming
things and judging me...

82
00:06:02,791 --> 00:06:05,051
and framing me in a weird way.
This isn't the first or second time.

83
00:06:05,121 --> 00:06:06,391
As long as we don't have
feelings for each other,

84
00:06:06,461 --> 00:06:07,461
that's all that matters.

85
00:06:07,521 --> 00:06:10,591
We shouldn't have to care
what anyone else thinks.

86
00:06:16,471 --> 00:06:17,471
Hey, Woo Jae.

87
00:06:18,271 --> 00:06:20,841
Right, don't come pick me up.
I'm not done with work yet,

88
00:06:20,901 --> 00:06:22,301
and I have a lot of stuff here,

89
00:06:22,371 --> 00:06:24,341
so one of the staff will
give me a ride. Okay, bye.

90
00:06:25,141 --> 00:06:26,811
You mean, me?

91
00:06:26,911 --> 00:06:28,681
Well, am I supposed to
carry all this myself?

92
00:06:28,741 --> 00:06:30,051
My grandfather stayed up all night,

93
00:06:30,111 --> 00:06:33,221
- to help you out for free.
- Who said anything about free?

94
00:06:33,251 --> 00:06:35,991
I'm going to officially pay
for the sample production.

95
00:06:42,891 --> 00:06:44,891
How did you two end up
coming home together?

96
00:06:44,961 --> 00:06:49,301
- I had a lovely dinner with Father.
- Oh, I see.

97
00:06:49,571 --> 00:06:51,431
Father, you left
work without a word.

98
00:06:51,501 --> 00:06:53,301
I see you were on a date with Se Ri.

99
00:06:53,601 --> 00:06:56,671
- I'm going to bed.
- Okay, Father. Good night.

100
00:06:57,271 --> 00:06:58,371
One more thing...

101
00:06:58,771 --> 00:06:59,781
Yes?

102
00:07:00,441 --> 00:07:02,011
It's about Hyun Bin.

103
00:07:02,311 --> 00:07:04,181
Yes. What about him?

104
00:07:05,311 --> 00:07:06,321
Never mind.

105
00:07:14,061 --> 00:07:16,961
Why would he stop
in the middle of saying something?

106
00:07:17,661 --> 00:07:18,661
Honey.

107
00:07:19,131 --> 00:07:22,331
Father said we should
get Hyun Bin married.

108
00:07:23,031 --> 00:07:25,271
Come on, you think that's possible?

109
00:07:25,771 --> 00:07:28,541
Hyun Bin said he has no interest
in seeing anyone ever again.

110
00:07:29,211 --> 00:07:31,371
And it hasn't been long since he broke up
with Jeong Han's daughter.

111
00:07:31,611 --> 00:07:33,381
I know.
But after they broke up, it seems...

112
00:07:33,441 --> 00:07:34,941
like they've become mortal enemies.

113
00:07:35,011 --> 00:07:37,451
- They fight constantly.
- They do?

114
00:07:39,781 --> 00:07:40,781
Why?

115
00:07:41,821 --> 00:07:45,491
If there were no feelings involved,
they wouldn't fight like that.

116
00:07:45,891 --> 00:07:48,821
If they were indifferent to each
other, they wouldn't even speak.

117
00:07:49,191 --> 00:07:50,291
Oh, excuse me. The bathroom.

118
00:07:55,201 --> 00:07:56,331
Is that right?

119
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:06,581
Are you sure? She really
tried to hit them with a car?

120
00:08:06,811 --> 00:08:10,211
Otherwise, why would Woo Jae
be picking me up day and night?

121
00:08:10,251 --> 00:08:12,381
We're going around
in pairs right now.

122
00:08:12,551 --> 00:08:14,481
Because we don't know
what that woman is capable of.

123
00:08:14,551 --> 00:08:17,721
Wow, she's completely
out of her mind.

124
00:08:18,951 --> 00:08:20,691
Where are you headed after work?

125
00:08:21,561 --> 00:08:23,061
My apartment. Why?

126
00:08:23,361 --> 00:08:26,901
Go to family's and sort it out.
So there won't be any gossip.

127
00:08:27,531 --> 00:08:30,231
There won't be any gossip,
so don't you worry.

128
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:32,231
There always has been.

129
00:08:41,081 --> 00:08:44,251
- What are you doing?
- I'll be lookout, take it inside.

130
00:08:44,481 --> 00:08:47,721
The least you could do
is help me put it down.

131
00:08:47,781 --> 00:08:49,691
That stuff is really heavy.

132
00:08:50,551 --> 00:08:54,421
Oh, but if your family sees us,
they might get the wrong idea again.

133
00:08:54,491 --> 00:08:56,231
There might be gossip...

134
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,931
What gossip? I'm just going to say
you're my porter.

135
00:08:58,931 --> 00:08:59,931
What?

136
00:09:00,231 --> 00:09:02,361
Just go. I'll be the lookout.

137
00:09:04,471 --> 00:09:05,471
Hurry.

138
00:09:10,771 --> 00:09:13,381
Oh. Gosh, this is heavy.

139
00:09:18,311 --> 00:09:19,721
Good job today.

140
00:09:20,421 --> 00:09:23,221
You are seriously so mean.

141
00:09:23,591 --> 00:09:24,721
Back to you!

142
00:09:24,721 --> 00:09:26,921
What did you just say?
You were bad-mouthing, weren't you?

143
00:09:27,321 --> 00:09:28,461
Go ahead.

144
00:09:47,381 --> 00:09:51,581
Grandfather, so you've never had
a cell phone this whole time?

145
00:09:52,881 --> 00:09:53,881
Right.

146
00:09:54,351 --> 00:09:57,521
- Tell me the family phone numbers.
- Oh, okay.

147
00:09:57,821 --> 00:10:02,321
I'll save everyone's numbers
for you and set up speed dial too.

148
00:10:02,391 --> 00:10:03,461
Speed dial?

149
00:10:04,361 --> 00:10:07,131
Oh, right. Just press
and hold one number,

150
00:10:07,201 --> 00:10:08,661
- and it'll make the call.
- I see.

151
00:10:09,971 --> 00:10:12,571
Number one will be
for Grandma, right?

152
00:10:12,941 --> 00:10:15,371
What should I save her name as?
Na Seon Hae?

153
00:10:18,841 --> 00:10:19,981
My wife.

154
00:10:23,211 --> 00:10:26,121
- Oh my, Grandfather.
- I'm home.

155
00:10:26,551 --> 00:10:31,091
- Oh my.
- Coming home alone this late?

156
00:10:31,151 --> 00:10:34,761
- Oh, no. A coworker came with me.
- A coworker?

157
00:10:34,961 --> 00:10:37,961
What?
Grandfather, you got a cell phone?

158
00:10:38,361 --> 00:10:40,261
Your Uncle Dae Han bought it for me.

159
00:10:40,461 --> 00:10:44,501
What? Uncle beat me to it.
I was going to buy you one.

160
00:10:44,731 --> 00:10:47,471
But sister,
did you bring more fabric?

161
00:10:47,971 --> 00:10:49,971
It's even more than last time.

162
00:10:50,311 --> 00:10:52,071
By any chance,

163
00:10:52,171 --> 00:10:55,911
could you help me make
the samples today too?

164
00:10:56,081 --> 00:10:59,781
Of course. I told you
I'd help you anytime.

165
00:11:00,851 --> 00:11:03,091
Seriously, you should
handle that yourself.

166
00:11:03,351 --> 00:11:04,651
Why are you making things
hard for Grandfather?

167
00:11:05,151 --> 00:11:06,721
No, it's fine. I enjoy doing it.

168
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:08,761
I have fun working
with my granddaughter.

169
00:11:09,561 --> 00:11:11,631
That's a relief.
I figured you'd say that,

170
00:11:11,691 --> 00:11:13,431
so to make it easier for you to see,

171
00:11:13,501 --> 00:11:15,861
I printed the work order
in large font.

172
00:11:15,931 --> 00:11:19,201
Really? Oh, that's great.
Put the fabric on the second floor.

173
00:11:19,271 --> 00:11:21,871
- I'll be right up.
- Grandfather, you're the best.

174
00:11:21,941 --> 00:11:24,271
I'll definitely repay you for this.

175
00:11:25,371 --> 00:11:28,111
Make sure you pay Grandfather
properly for his work, okay?

176
00:11:28,941 --> 00:11:31,551
Hey, don't talk to
your sister like that.

177
00:11:32,211 --> 00:11:34,781
Serves you right.
Grandfather is the best.

178
00:11:35,521 --> 00:11:38,091
But look at how she's talking.

179
00:11:38,951 --> 00:11:40,391
- I'm going up.
- Why hit me?

180
00:11:40,491 --> 00:11:43,231
You rascal. I'm doing
this because I want to.

181
00:11:48,561 --> 00:11:51,171
What are you planning
to do with this?

182
00:11:51,901 --> 00:11:53,871
Reminiscence therapy
for Father's memory.

183
00:11:55,401 --> 00:11:56,411
Thank you.

184
00:11:56,771 --> 00:11:58,371
Even though you're going
through a hard time,

185
00:11:58,441 --> 00:11:59,781
you're still taking
care of my father.

186
00:12:00,381 --> 00:12:02,211
I do it because I enjoy it.

187
00:12:02,541 --> 00:12:05,051
And it's rewarding to see
Father recovering.

188
00:12:06,111 --> 00:12:08,151
But you know, he's recovering
really fast.

189
00:12:08,421 --> 00:12:11,251
I know. He's so motivated too.

190
00:12:11,891 --> 00:12:14,621
I'm going to my radiation
therapy with Woo Jae tomorrow.

191
00:12:15,521 --> 00:12:18,091
I should have made time
for that. I'm sorry.

192
00:12:18,461 --> 00:12:22,361
It's fine. I could've gone alone,
but because of that woman...

193
00:12:22,631 --> 00:12:23,771
Tell me about it.

194
00:12:25,401 --> 00:12:27,541
We really need to catch
her soon. We really do.

195
00:12:32,411 --> 00:12:35,581
You have to charge it so you can
use it tomorrow. Give it here.

196
00:12:36,211 --> 00:12:37,211
There.

197
00:12:43,091 --> 00:12:44,491
"Good night. My wife."

198
00:12:44,951 --> 00:12:48,021
Oh, my, you learned
how to send texts?

199
00:12:48,491 --> 00:12:50,491
I'll send you a lot more tomorrow.

200
00:12:51,961 --> 00:12:53,231
Can you sleep alone?

201
00:12:53,661 --> 00:12:54,661
What?

202
00:12:55,061 --> 00:12:59,641
Oh, I mean, won't you be scared?
I want to go help my granddaughter.

203
00:13:00,701 --> 00:13:03,571
I lived alone for 30 years.
What's there to be scared of?

204
00:13:04,071 --> 00:13:05,211
That's true.

205
00:13:16,351 --> 00:13:18,221
Your white blood cell count
is quite high.

206
00:13:18,521 --> 00:13:20,121
And you're already showing
signs of purpura.

207
00:13:20,691 --> 00:13:22,991
You need to go to a major hospital
with your family...

208
00:13:23,061 --> 00:13:25,191
without delay and get
a bone marrow test.

209
00:13:34,371 --> 00:13:35,641
Were there a lot of customers today?

210
00:13:36,241 --> 00:13:37,771
Yes, it was okay.

211
00:13:38,471 --> 00:13:42,041
- I'm busy preparing the new menu.
- I see.

212
00:13:42,981 --> 00:13:44,251
Is there anything I can do to help?

213
00:13:47,221 --> 00:13:51,091
- Should we have a baby?
- Gosh.

214
00:13:52,051 --> 00:13:53,691
Why are you being like
this again? Dolphin.

215
00:13:54,061 --> 00:13:57,231
I just thought it would be
nice if we had a child, too.

216
00:13:57,891 --> 00:14:00,001
Even you were fawning
over the baby yesterday.

217
00:14:00,161 --> 00:14:02,801
What baby in the world isn't cute?

218
00:14:03,201 --> 00:14:05,771
Still, if we actually had one,
I bet Tamin would adore them.

219
00:14:06,131 --> 00:14:07,141
Why are you like this...

220
00:14:07,201 --> 00:14:08,941
after we already went to
the OB-GYN and got tested?

221
00:14:09,911 --> 00:14:13,741
They said it would be difficult,
not impossible.

222
00:14:14,911 --> 00:14:17,481
It's not impossible,
but it is difficult.

223
00:14:20,051 --> 00:14:22,021
Don't get any funny ideas. Got it?

224
00:14:22,081 --> 00:14:25,391
For me, our Ji Hu is
more than enough.

225
00:14:26,221 --> 00:14:29,521
Gosh, whatever.
I should get to sleep.

226
00:14:31,731 --> 00:14:33,101
Oh, this is nice.

227
00:14:42,241 --> 00:14:45,771
By the way, how old did you say
you were this year?

228
00:14:46,341 --> 00:14:50,381
I was two
when you disappeared, Grandfather.

229
00:14:51,251 --> 00:14:52,811
They said you adored me.

230
00:14:53,121 --> 00:14:54,421
You're still adorable.

231
00:14:55,581 --> 00:14:57,351
But I guess you don't
have a boyfriend?

232
00:14:58,351 --> 00:14:59,351
No.

233
00:14:59,421 --> 00:15:03,991
You're so pretty,
talented, and smart,

234
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:05,491
and you don't have a partner?

235
00:15:05,791 --> 00:15:08,231
Oh, do you really need a partner?

236
00:15:08,631 --> 00:15:12,501
Well, it's good to have someone.
To be with you when it's dangerous.

237
00:15:12,731 --> 00:15:15,141
It's fine, Woo Jae comes
to get me. Don't worry.

238
00:15:15,401 --> 00:15:19,011
I'm sorry for putting
the family through so much trouble.

239
00:15:19,111 --> 00:15:21,841
Grandfather, no more apologies.

240
00:15:22,341 --> 00:15:27,021
I have a phone now,
so call when Woo Jae can't come.

241
00:15:27,081 --> 00:15:28,321
I'll come get you.

242
00:15:28,551 --> 00:15:31,651
You promised.
No taking it back later.

243
00:15:31,891 --> 00:15:35,121
Well, I'll only pick you up
until you find a partner.

244
00:15:35,321 --> 00:15:38,091
I told you, I don't need a partner.

245
00:15:53,941 --> 00:15:56,581
I think I did get injured.

246
00:16:06,961 --> 00:16:08,391
- Oh my.
- Gosh, my back.

247
00:16:35,951 --> 00:16:41,191
From now on,
please call me Stylist Yang.

248
00:16:41,621 --> 00:16:45,961
- What? Did you get a job?
- Yes, I have a job now.

249
00:16:46,801 --> 00:16:50,971
- Congratulations, sweetie.
- Mom, I'm sorry I can't help you.

250
00:16:51,031 --> 00:16:53,101
It's okay. I've been getting
so many customers anyway,

251
00:16:53,201 --> 00:16:55,471
so I hired a full-time
employee and a part-timer.

252
00:16:55,701 --> 00:16:57,311
From now on, honey,
just do your best...

253
00:16:57,341 --> 00:16:59,411
to follow your dreams.
I'll be cheering for you.

254
00:17:00,411 --> 00:17:03,451
Hey, Yang Eun Bin,
what was that? A stylist?

255
00:17:03,511 --> 00:17:04,511
What's that?

256
00:17:04,581 --> 00:17:08,181
Yes, you coordinate outfits
for celebrities and famous people.

257
00:17:08,381 --> 00:17:10,721
But, didn't you say
you wanted to be an influencer?

258
00:17:11,151 --> 00:17:12,251
I do.

259
00:17:12,351 --> 00:17:15,291
But I realized I need to figure out
what I really want to do first.

260
00:17:15,591 --> 00:17:17,361
I can't just jump
in blindly and blow...

261
00:17:17,431 --> 00:17:19,431
all the startup money
Grandfather gave me.

262
00:17:19,801 --> 00:17:20,801
That's smart.

263
00:17:21,201 --> 00:17:23,671
I know, right? My smart girl.

264
00:17:24,371 --> 00:17:27,501
Anyway, take a good look at my face.

265
00:17:27,571 --> 00:17:29,641
Because I'm about to get super busy.

266
00:17:29,841 --> 00:17:34,681
Leave your style to me.
Stylist Yang.

267
00:17:35,711 --> 00:17:37,511
So cool, my daughter.

268
00:17:38,511 --> 00:17:41,021
Dad, that shirt gets
a failing grade.

269
00:17:47,491 --> 00:17:48,491
This must be the place.

270
00:17:50,391 --> 00:17:53,061
I'm so nervous. No, I can do this.

271
00:17:53,861 --> 00:17:54,861
I can do this.

272
00:17:57,871 --> 00:17:59,841
- For the interview, Yang Eun Bin.
- Yes?

273
00:17:59,901 --> 00:18:01,801
- You're hired, starting today.
- What?

274
00:18:01,871 --> 00:18:03,841
The newbie who was supposed to
do pickups today ghosted us.

275
00:18:04,271 --> 00:18:05,371
Just quit without a word.

276
00:18:07,441 --> 00:18:09,641
- Get in.
- What? Okay!

277
00:18:19,751 --> 00:18:21,461
Wait, wait for me.

278
00:18:27,301 --> 00:18:28,901
- Hurry up.
- Okay.

279
00:18:30,571 --> 00:18:32,701
- This way.
- Sorry.

280
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:35,671
Unbelievable.

281
00:18:42,081 --> 00:18:44,081
- Can't you do anything right?
- Sorry.

282
00:18:44,151 --> 00:18:46,451
Yes, I'm heading to the site now.
I'll be there in 20.

283
00:18:46,751 --> 00:18:49,451
- Newbie, can you drive?
- Yes, I can.

284
00:18:49,521 --> 00:18:53,021
- What're you waiting for? Let's go.
- Oh, yes, I'm coming.

285
00:18:56,931 --> 00:18:58,161
Wow.

286
00:18:59,361 --> 00:19:01,061
The quality is insane.

287
00:19:02,731 --> 00:19:04,901
Your grandfather's skills
are incredible.

288
00:19:05,501 --> 00:19:08,971
- Right?
- On par with any sample room.

289
00:19:09,271 --> 00:19:12,611
Don't just brush this off
as a family favor, CEO Gong,

290
00:19:12,671 --> 00:19:14,641
calculate the proper labor
cost and bill us for it.

291
00:19:14,741 --> 00:19:15,911
Yes, Vice President.

292
00:19:16,081 --> 00:19:19,481
- Should we find a factory?
- Yes, let's do that.

293
00:19:20,151 --> 00:19:23,451
I've scheduled a meeting
with the platform's marketing team.

294
00:19:24,721 --> 00:19:25,991
If we can
just get on their platform,

295
00:19:26,051 --> 00:19:27,191
we'll be able to breathe a little.

296
00:19:27,561 --> 00:19:30,161
Director Yang, what if we take
photos of the main looks...

297
00:19:30,231 --> 00:19:34,701
- and include them in the proposal?
- The meeting is tomorrow.

298
00:19:35,001 --> 00:19:37,071
When would we have time
to cast a model and do a shoot?

299
00:19:37,471 --> 00:19:38,531
Why cast anyone?

300
00:19:39,431 --> 00:19:40,541
We have models right here.

301
00:19:41,171 --> 00:19:42,271
What?

302
00:19:44,541 --> 00:19:46,471
CEO Gong and Director Yang can wear
the samples for the photos.

303
00:19:50,651 --> 00:19:51,911
As a couple concept.

304
00:19:53,521 --> 00:19:55,381
- No way.
- No way.

305
00:19:55,451 --> 00:19:57,721
Why not? I think it'd be fun.

306
00:19:58,251 --> 00:19:59,691
You both have
the right physique for it.

307
00:19:59,991 --> 00:20:02,121
The physical samples are enough.

308
00:20:02,191 --> 00:20:05,731
That's right. I can explain
the design intent myself.

309
00:20:05,831 --> 00:20:09,301
That's ridiculous. Having photos
of someone wearing it...

310
00:20:09,361 --> 00:20:10,831
is obviously better
for showing the details,

311
00:20:10,901 --> 00:20:13,171
and you both know it helps people
understand the product better.

312
00:20:13,231 --> 00:20:16,141
Exactly. How unprofessional.

313
00:20:17,971 --> 00:20:19,041
Oh my.

314
00:20:19,071 --> 00:20:20,111
You two are doing the shoot.

315
00:20:20,111 --> 00:20:21,511
- But we...
- It's just that...

316
00:20:22,681 --> 00:20:24,051
- But still...
- As you guys all know...

317
00:20:34,421 --> 00:20:37,561
Get closer, you two. It's a couple
concept, not an enemies concept.

318
00:20:37,661 --> 00:20:38,661
I said, it's a concept.

319
00:20:39,291 --> 00:20:43,331
- I just can't get into character.
- You think I'm enjoying this?

320
00:20:45,071 --> 00:20:47,741
You were all over each other
when you were dating. Good grief.

321
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:49,601
- Hey. What...
- Come on, get over here.

322
00:20:49,871 --> 00:20:51,871
Come here. There.

323
00:20:53,171 --> 00:20:56,241
Mind control, people. We are dating.

324
00:20:56,341 --> 00:20:58,411
We are in love.

325
00:20:59,451 --> 00:21:02,781
- This won't do.
- Let's just get this over with.

326
00:21:03,351 --> 00:21:05,391
- You confident?
- About what?

327
00:21:05,451 --> 00:21:08,491
- That you won't fall for me.
- You're unbelievable.

328
00:21:15,961 --> 00:21:20,441
That's the spirit. Great. One, two.

329
00:21:20,901 --> 00:21:23,711
Let me know if your heart's about
to burst. I can tone it down for you.

330
00:21:24,111 --> 00:21:26,171
No matter how much
you come on to me,

331
00:21:26,241 --> 00:21:27,911
my heart rate won't budge an inch.

332
00:21:30,451 --> 00:21:32,851
I can hear your heart
pounding from over here.

333
00:21:35,481 --> 00:21:37,821
Okay, lips. Can you pout a little?

334
00:21:37,891 --> 00:21:40,791
Pout, like this.
Oh, so pretty. So pretty.

335
00:21:40,861 --> 00:21:44,191
So pretty. I really love it.

336
00:21:44,631 --> 00:21:46,591
- Show off that jawline.
- Look at them, having so much fun.

337
00:21:46,661 --> 00:21:47,731
- Beautiful.
- Gosh,

338
00:21:47,731 --> 00:21:51,201
I want to join the fun too.
What am I even doing?

339
00:21:51,271 --> 00:21:53,571
Just sitting here
keeping watch. Gosh.

340
00:21:57,471 --> 00:22:00,481
- Watch where you're going.
- It's hot. Why are you so close?

341
00:22:00,611 --> 00:22:01,611
Seriously.

342
00:22:02,511 --> 00:22:03,511
So,

343
00:22:04,051 --> 00:22:05,311
should we get something to eat?

344
00:22:11,591 --> 00:22:12,821
Vice President.

345
00:22:24,771 --> 00:22:25,801
Pacu Nacho!

346
00:22:27,501 --> 00:22:29,101
Are you okay?

347
00:22:29,341 --> 00:22:32,111
No, I'm not okay. My bone.
I think it's broken.

348
00:22:32,171 --> 00:22:34,881
- Oh no, what do we do?
- Let me take a look.

349
00:22:36,851 --> 00:22:38,881
It's not broken.
If it were a fracture,

350
00:22:38,951 --> 00:22:40,821
you'd be screaming in pain
at the slightest touch.

351
00:22:41,421 --> 00:22:44,521
Ouch. It hurts!

352
00:22:45,751 --> 00:22:49,261
The hospital. We have to go
to the hospital. Right?

353
00:22:49,321 --> 00:22:52,391
- I'll head out. Go on your own.
- What?

354
00:22:52,691 --> 00:22:54,801
- Just go.
- Gosh, it hurts.

355
00:22:55,031 --> 00:22:58,871
- It does?
- Gosh. I said it hurts.

356
00:22:58,931 --> 00:22:59,931
Gosh...

357
00:23:04,711 --> 00:23:08,711
Father, there's no need to
force yourself to remember.

358
00:23:08,741 --> 00:23:10,381
As you look at these items,

359
00:23:10,381 --> 00:23:12,381
if any words or feelings
come to mind,

360
00:23:12,451 --> 00:23:14,721
just feel free to tell me.

361
00:23:21,721 --> 00:23:24,861
When Ju Ah's dad was little,
he said he wanted to become...

362
00:23:24,861 --> 00:23:26,791
a great doctor
just like you, Father.

363
00:23:26,931 --> 00:23:29,101
He told me that you gave
this to him as a gift.

364
00:23:29,561 --> 00:23:30,671
Oh, really?

365
00:23:31,501 --> 00:23:36,141
Oh, he wanted to be like me?
I must have been a good doctor.

366
00:23:36,941 --> 00:23:37,941
Yes.

367
00:23:39,441 --> 00:23:41,441
Okay, next up...

368
00:23:41,841 --> 00:23:44,011
is this.

369
00:23:47,351 --> 00:23:48,621
What comes to mind?

370
00:23:49,321 --> 00:23:51,491
Is this some allowance
money I gave to someone?

371
00:23:51,621 --> 00:23:53,921
Oh my, that's right, Father.

372
00:23:54,391 --> 00:23:56,761
When Dae Han came home
on leave from the army,

373
00:23:56,861 --> 00:24:01,101
- the last allowance you gave him.
- Oh, dear.

374
00:24:01,661 --> 00:24:05,231
He kept this for 30 years?

375
00:24:06,301 --> 00:24:10,771
He said he was afraid that if he
spent it, he'd never see you again.

376
00:24:16,511 --> 00:24:19,811
<i>My darling love, once so kind</i>

377
00:24:19,811 --> 00:24:22,581
<i>Have you forgotten me?</i>

378
00:24:23,481 --> 00:24:27,461
How did you come to like this song?

379
00:24:27,591 --> 00:24:28,761
Do you remember?

380
00:24:29,591 --> 00:24:33,061
One day, someone was
singing this on TV,

381
00:24:33,531 --> 00:24:35,901
and I started crying
before I knew it.

382
00:24:36,431 --> 00:24:38,401
I've been listening
to it ever since.

383
00:24:38,971 --> 00:24:40,201
This song...

384
00:24:40,441 --> 00:24:44,641
You used to sing it
to Mother a lot, Father.

385
00:24:46,671 --> 00:24:49,541
Is that why my heart ached
whenever I heard this song?

386
00:24:49,881 --> 00:24:53,281
Yes. There must have been
a longing you weren't even aware of,

387
00:24:53,381 --> 00:24:55,221
in your heart.

388
00:24:56,521 --> 00:24:59,021
But why can't I remember anything?

389
00:24:59,991 --> 00:25:02,291
There's no need to be anxious.

390
00:25:02,361 --> 00:25:06,061
This is just an exercise
for you to realize...

391
00:25:06,061 --> 00:25:08,701
who you were, Father,
and the person you were.

392
00:25:12,871 --> 00:25:15,401
Oh, right. You have
to go to the hospital.

393
00:25:15,471 --> 00:25:17,641
You said you had radiation therapy
or something, didn't you?

394
00:25:18,111 --> 00:25:20,141
Yes, once Gong Woo Jae comes down.

395
00:25:20,811 --> 00:25:23,111
- What about you, Father?
- I have to go to the hospital too.

396
00:25:23,181 --> 00:25:25,111
I'll watch the examinations
and hang out with my friend.

397
00:25:33,891 --> 00:25:35,591
I wonder if she got to work okay.

398
00:25:37,591 --> 00:25:38,691
Woo Jae.

399
00:25:39,261 --> 00:25:40,701
Yes, I'm coming.

400
00:25:55,111 --> 00:25:56,341
Woo Jae, my in-law.

401
00:25:57,281 --> 00:26:00,151
Eun Bin, congratulations
on your first day. How's work?

402
00:26:00,651 --> 00:26:01,821
(Eun Bin, congratulations
on your first day. How's work?)

403
00:26:01,951 --> 00:26:04,951
Hey, rookie.
Are you going to take all day?

404
00:26:05,591 --> 00:26:07,361
Yes, coming!

405
00:26:07,621 --> 00:26:10,021
- Hurry up and bring it over.
- Yes, coming!

406
00:26:10,861 --> 00:26:12,791
- Faster.
- Yes.

407
00:26:13,961 --> 00:26:16,461
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

408
00:26:18,071 --> 00:26:21,371
What, you mean, right here? Here?

409
00:26:22,471 --> 00:26:24,071
Yes, right there, Dr. Gong.
That part.

410
00:26:24,141 --> 00:26:25,771
I think that's
the part that's broken.

411
00:26:26,541 --> 00:26:28,811
What am I going to do
if I can never use my arm again?

412
00:26:29,811 --> 00:26:33,251
- You're being so dramatic...
- What do you mean, dramatic?

413
00:26:33,311 --> 00:26:36,221
Oh my, how did you
get hurt like that?

414
00:26:36,321 --> 00:26:38,851
I got hurt like this
while saving your granddaughter...

415
00:26:38,921 --> 00:26:40,291
from being hit by a scooter.

416
00:26:40,291 --> 00:26:41,761
Is that right?

417
00:26:43,891 --> 00:26:45,361
Oh, so you're the grandfather.

418
00:26:45,691 --> 00:26:47,501
- Hello.
- Oh, hello.

419
00:26:47,561 --> 00:26:50,001
He's the grandson from
the Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.

420
00:26:50,501 --> 00:26:52,731
I see. Nice to meet you.

421
00:26:53,601 --> 00:26:55,401
You're a handsome young man.

422
00:26:55,401 --> 00:26:57,441
You don't take after
your grandfather.

423
00:26:59,641 --> 00:27:01,311
You're quite the joker, Grandfather.

424
00:27:03,881 --> 00:27:06,181
Well, this is strange.

425
00:27:06,251 --> 00:27:09,381
No matter how I look at it,
this isn't a fracture.

426
00:27:09,451 --> 00:27:12,891
Oh, that can't be right.
Please, take another look.

427
00:27:13,021 --> 00:27:17,131
There's no swelling or deformity,
and this joint moves just fine.

428
00:27:17,331 --> 00:27:20,661
It's not a fracture,
just a minor ligament injury.

429
00:27:20,761 --> 00:27:23,701
Stop trying to scam us.
I ought to just break it for you.

430
00:27:23,971 --> 00:27:26,401
Gong Ju Ah. Watch your language.

431
00:27:26,901 --> 00:27:31,041
Ma'am, did you see that?
Your granddaughter is so hostile.

432
00:27:31,611 --> 00:27:34,641
Hey, is that any way to treat
the person who saved your life?

433
00:27:34,811 --> 00:27:37,851
To hear you talk, anyone would
think you actually saved my life.

434
00:27:37,911 --> 00:27:39,551
He practically did save your life.

435
00:27:39,611 --> 00:27:41,681
Those scooters are
so dangerous these days.

436
00:27:41,751 --> 00:27:44,721
Right?
You're a reasonable man, Father.

437
00:27:44,751 --> 00:27:46,821
Of course I am.

438
00:27:47,291 --> 00:27:49,561
But you're just being
a baby about it.

439
00:27:50,191 --> 00:27:52,131
What do you mean, a baby?

440
00:27:52,731 --> 00:27:54,531
- Hey, young man.
- Yes, Grandfather?

441
00:27:56,131 --> 00:27:57,771
- What...
- Nice catch.

442
00:27:58,701 --> 00:27:59,831
See? You're perfectly fine.

443
00:28:00,401 --> 00:28:02,441
Come on, Grandfather...

444
00:28:02,501 --> 00:28:05,211
Wow, look at that. You've got
great reflexes, don't you?

445
00:28:05,371 --> 00:28:07,741
I'll prescribe you
some anti-inflammatory painkillers.

446
00:28:07,841 --> 00:28:09,581
Just make sure
to take them, all right?

447
00:28:09,641 --> 00:28:11,881
But it really did hurt...

448
00:28:11,951 --> 00:28:14,881
You're just like your father,
making a big fuss over nothing.

449
00:28:15,851 --> 00:28:17,721
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

450
00:28:17,821 --> 00:28:20,761
I'm starting to think
your father's a quack.

451
00:28:20,961 --> 00:28:22,191
That's right, he's a quack.

452
00:28:23,291 --> 00:28:25,761
- Right, Grandfather?
- Yes. Let's get some acupuncture.

453
00:28:25,831 --> 00:28:27,091
- What?
- Get some acupuncture.

454
00:28:27,161 --> 00:28:28,161
Grandfather...

455
00:28:28,461 --> 00:28:29,561
Oh, honestly...

456
00:28:29,631 --> 00:28:31,101
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

457
00:28:31,731 --> 00:28:33,871
- A scooter?
- Yes.

458
00:28:33,941 --> 00:28:35,541
How is it? Do you think it's broken?

459
00:28:35,901 --> 00:28:39,271
It's not broken. Just a sprain.

460
00:28:40,681 --> 00:28:43,381
That's strange.
I'm sure it's broken.

461
00:28:43,581 --> 00:28:46,381
Go ahead and call him a quack now.

462
00:28:47,221 --> 00:28:49,051
Grandfather,
please take one more look.

463
00:28:49,121 --> 00:28:50,351
I'm telling you,
I really think it's broken.

464
00:28:50,421 --> 00:28:51,421
Get out.

465
00:28:53,751 --> 00:28:54,761
Please leave.

466
00:28:55,391 --> 00:28:58,061
You punk. Follow me.
I'll give you acupuncture.

467
00:29:02,261 --> 00:29:03,261
Oh, man.

468
00:29:06,331 --> 00:29:07,541
Why did you tag along?

469
00:29:07,871 --> 00:29:09,401
Did you finish
the Memory Tonic already?

470
00:29:11,311 --> 00:29:13,241
Hey, Seon Chul, the thing is...

471
00:29:13,611 --> 00:29:16,681
Your grandson,
he isn't married yet, is he?

472
00:29:17,081 --> 00:29:21,451
- Why do you ask?
- We should set him up with Ju Ah.

473
00:29:23,051 --> 00:29:25,591
When is your memory coming back?

474
00:29:25,851 --> 00:29:29,691
- My memory? Why?
- How long will you spout nonsense?

475
00:29:30,561 --> 00:29:33,361
Your second daughter-in-law,
Dong Suk...

476
00:29:33,691 --> 00:29:35,131
is my daughter.

477
00:29:36,231 --> 00:29:37,231
Really?

478
00:29:38,131 --> 00:29:39,231
She's your daughter?

479
00:29:40,641 --> 00:29:43,101
- So we're in-laws?
- Yes.

480
00:29:44,571 --> 00:29:45,711
Not a chance. No double in-laws.

481
00:29:46,211 --> 00:29:48,911
Right?
I got my hopes up for nothing.

482
00:29:50,711 --> 00:29:53,481
Oh, right.
Have you had a blood test?

483
00:29:53,811 --> 00:29:54,881
What?

484
00:29:55,951 --> 00:29:58,821
- I don't know.
- What do you mean you don't know?

485
00:29:59,451 --> 00:30:02,321
Come on, get a blood test.
Let's do it at our hospital.

486
00:30:02,391 --> 00:30:03,391
Forget it.

487
00:30:07,661 --> 00:30:10,701
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

488
00:30:11,871 --> 00:30:13,031
Mr. Gong Gi Cheol?

489
00:30:13,701 --> 00:30:16,701
- Yes.
- A woman over there...

490
00:30:17,001 --> 00:30:18,211
asked me to give this to you.

491
00:30:33,691 --> 00:30:34,761
Mun Sik.

492
00:30:35,261 --> 00:30:37,961
It's me. Your sister, Mi Hyang.

493
00:30:39,391 --> 00:30:41,431
You still don't remember anything,
do you?

494
00:30:42,401 --> 00:30:44,471
It's not that
you've lost your memory.

495
00:30:44,831 --> 00:30:47,171
You can't remember
because they're not your memories.

496
00:30:47,841 --> 00:30:51,371
Those people are lying to you.

497
00:30:53,071 --> 00:30:55,581
I've always told you, haven't I?

498
00:30:56,211 --> 00:30:57,451
That you should only trust me.

499
00:30:58,311 --> 00:31:01,821
I hid and took care
of you for 30 years.

500
00:31:02,481 --> 00:31:04,421
Please, don't let them fool you.

501
00:31:05,091 --> 00:31:06,221
Your name is...

502
00:31:06,691 --> 00:31:07,761
Jo Mun Sik.

503
00:31:18,331 --> 00:31:19,971
Mom, are you okay?

504
00:31:20,471 --> 00:31:22,741
No, I feel a little...

505
00:31:23,501 --> 00:31:24,511
Nauseous?

506
00:31:25,611 --> 00:31:26,641
I'm fine.

507
00:31:27,481 --> 00:31:28,481
What about your part-time job?

508
00:31:28,981 --> 00:31:30,751
If I drop you off first,
I'll be right on time.

509
00:31:35,481 --> 00:31:36,651
Now what?

510
00:31:40,721 --> 00:31:41,721
Hello?

511
00:31:42,391 --> 00:31:43,391
- Yes.
- Thank you.

512
00:31:43,461 --> 00:31:45,131
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

513
00:31:45,791 --> 00:31:48,331
(3H Acupressure Bed)

514
00:31:48,461 --> 00:31:50,331
Business must be doing pretty well.

515
00:31:51,271 --> 00:31:54,141
I guess I just have a knack
for bringing in customers.

516
00:31:54,871 --> 00:31:58,571
So, what did you
want to see me about?

517
00:32:03,141 --> 00:32:05,811
Oh, my, Dr. Han, are you all right?

518
00:32:06,111 --> 00:32:07,421
Yes.

519
00:32:07,981 --> 00:32:09,751
I was just coming from a treatment.

520
00:32:10,381 --> 00:32:13,221
Oh, I see. Oh, dear.

521
00:32:13,851 --> 00:32:16,591
In that case,
I'll get straight to the point.

522
00:32:17,931 --> 00:32:18,931
Okay.

523
00:32:19,191 --> 00:32:21,431
I was...

524
00:32:22,001 --> 00:32:23,831
just so worried.

525
00:32:24,401 --> 00:32:26,571
About your daughter
and our Hyun Bin,

526
00:32:26,871 --> 00:32:28,501
and if we can just let things
go on like this...

527
00:32:28,871 --> 00:32:32,311
I thought you called to discuss
their marriage counseling...

528
00:32:32,571 --> 00:32:35,181
Well, I wasn't going to bring it up.

529
00:32:35,711 --> 00:32:38,051
But I happened to see
them yesterday,

530
00:32:38,151 --> 00:32:40,651
and they were
at each other's throats.

531
00:32:40,751 --> 00:32:41,751
And?

532
00:32:42,751 --> 00:32:46,521
- What's wrong with them fighting?
- Dr. Han, you know how people are.

533
00:32:46,921 --> 00:32:48,891
You know what they say, there's
a thin line between love and hate.

534
00:32:49,761 --> 00:32:52,061
I trust my Ju Ah.

535
00:32:53,161 --> 00:32:56,101
I don't want to discuss
this any further.

536
00:32:57,031 --> 00:32:58,031
Dr. Han.

537
00:32:58,301 --> 00:33:01,801
In that case, how about
I set your daughter up on a date?

538
00:33:02,641 --> 00:33:04,911
- What?
- If she misses her window,

539
00:33:04,971 --> 00:33:07,411
it'll be much harder
to find her a husband later.

540
00:33:07,581 --> 00:33:09,511
Besides, your daughter
is older than my Hyun Bin...

541
00:33:09,581 --> 00:33:12,151
Excuse me.
My Ju Ah looks young for her age.

542
00:33:12,681 --> 00:33:15,821
Besides, she's capable.
She can marry whenever she wants.

543
00:33:16,081 --> 00:33:18,491
Don't be so complacent.
You might regret it later.

544
00:33:18,551 --> 00:33:19,551
Hey!

545
00:33:20,291 --> 00:33:21,591
You startled me.

546
00:33:21,761 --> 00:33:24,131
If you bring up our children's
business one more time,

547
00:33:24,331 --> 00:33:27,361
I'm washing my hands
of this marriage counseling.

548
00:33:35,571 --> 00:33:38,711
Prestigious university abroad,
an executive at Taehan Group...

549
00:33:39,911 --> 00:33:42,741
With specs and looks like these,

550
00:33:43,181 --> 00:33:44,981
he should be in the highest tier
for a husband, right?

551
00:33:45,251 --> 00:33:47,081
There are some detracting factors,

552
00:33:47,951 --> 00:33:49,321
so he'll be moved down a tier.

553
00:33:50,051 --> 00:33:53,121
I see on his file
that his parents are divorced.

554
00:33:56,221 --> 00:33:59,431
In this day and age,
how is a divorce considered a flaw?

555
00:33:59,631 --> 00:34:01,131
It's not just our agency.

556
00:34:01,131 --> 00:34:03,561
Most VIP members
at matchmaking agencies...

557
00:34:03,661 --> 00:34:04,771
see a stable family background...

558
00:34:04,771 --> 00:34:06,801
as the number one indicator
of a person's character.

559
00:34:10,141 --> 00:34:14,211
Surely you can downplay
that risk for me, Manager.

560
00:34:14,581 --> 00:34:18,381
However, to sign up, you'll need
to come back with your son.

561
00:34:18,551 --> 00:34:21,381
My son is busy,
so I came on his behalf.

562
00:34:21,751 --> 00:34:23,581
We can't proceed
without his consent.

563
00:34:24,051 --> 00:34:25,921
It's the same
at any other matchmaking agency.

564
00:34:30,291 --> 00:34:32,431
So Hye, any luck with the factory?

565
00:34:34,091 --> 00:34:35,561
Really?

566
00:34:36,401 --> 00:34:38,471
Okay, I'll talk to Director Yang.

567
00:34:38,471 --> 00:34:39,931
You can all
just head home from there.

568
00:34:40,301 --> 00:34:41,301
Okay.

569
00:34:42,771 --> 00:34:45,041
What's wrong?
Couldn't they find a factory?

570
00:34:45,511 --> 00:34:47,541
No, they found one.

571
00:34:47,611 --> 00:34:50,281
But they're quoting a high price
because our order is too small.

572
00:34:51,311 --> 00:34:55,021
Then let's increase the quantity
and ask them to lower the price.

573
00:34:55,251 --> 00:34:57,321
I'm still in contact with investors,

574
00:34:57,381 --> 00:34:59,921
so we should be able to
secure more funding.

575
00:35:01,161 --> 00:35:03,421
I don't know where you get
all this confidence from.

576
00:35:04,361 --> 00:35:06,431
I believe in myself.

577
00:35:06,831 --> 00:35:08,261
My ability to see through
the current trends...

578
00:35:09,401 --> 00:35:11,131
Well, I'm heading home for the day.

579
00:35:11,201 --> 00:35:12,401
Heading home?
What are you talking about?

580
00:35:12,771 --> 00:35:15,541
We need to edit the proposal
and add the photos of the outfits.

581
00:35:16,871 --> 00:35:18,611
- Me?
- Well, should I do it?

582
00:35:18,871 --> 00:35:19,871
My arm hurts, you know?

583
00:35:19,941 --> 00:35:22,211
This happened when saving your life,
remember?

584
00:35:26,551 --> 00:35:28,021
(Pelliv Pursues
A Universal Beauty For All)

585
00:35:30,221 --> 00:35:32,421
Not that picture.
Use the second shot.

586
00:35:33,391 --> 00:35:34,391
Like this?

587
00:35:36,061 --> 00:35:38,691
No, on second thought,
the first shot is better.

588
00:35:41,901 --> 00:35:42,901
There. Happy?

589
00:35:43,461 --> 00:35:44,831
Sorry, change it back.

590
00:35:45,471 --> 00:35:47,941
Stop making me jump through hoops
like a trained mutt.

591
00:35:48,041 --> 00:35:49,501
Hey, put some effort into it.

592
00:35:49,571 --> 00:35:51,841
At least you're better than a mutt,
CEO Gong.

593
00:35:54,811 --> 00:35:56,811
Hurry up with this.

594
00:35:59,411 --> 00:36:00,511
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

595
00:36:06,521 --> 00:36:08,291
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

596
00:36:08,361 --> 00:36:09,491
(We are with you
to the end of your journey)

597
00:36:09,621 --> 00:36:14,191
It won't be easy, but it's not
impossible for you to get pregnant.

598
00:36:14,901 --> 00:36:17,431
Let's try ovulation-inducing drugs,
and we'll check...

599
00:36:17,501 --> 00:36:19,571
for follicle growth
at your next appointment.

600
00:36:20,231 --> 00:36:23,141
Maintain a regular sleep schedule.

601
00:36:23,271 --> 00:36:25,711
Must wear sleep socks.

602
00:36:27,641 --> 00:36:29,741
Keep my lower body warm.

603
00:36:30,611 --> 00:36:33,281
Then I guess cold foods
are bad for me.

604
00:36:35,621 --> 00:36:37,081
What? What are you looking at?

605
00:36:37,621 --> 00:36:39,621
I was just wondering
what you were doing.

606
00:36:39,951 --> 00:36:42,621
It's just my shopping list.

607
00:36:42,891 --> 00:36:44,491
Oh, really?

608
00:36:45,031 --> 00:36:46,031
I'll go buy them for you then.

609
00:36:46,331 --> 00:36:49,331
No, no. I'll get it.
Just keep working.

610
00:36:50,761 --> 00:36:51,771
Okay.

611
00:36:59,771 --> 00:37:01,941
Keep my lower body warm.
So, lower body...

612
00:37:02,481 --> 00:37:04,141
Okay. Good work.

613
00:37:04,981 --> 00:37:06,251
Make sure to lock up
before you leave.

614
00:37:06,681 --> 00:37:07,681
Okay.

615
00:37:08,921 --> 00:37:10,921
(Healthy Side Dish)

616
00:37:11,851 --> 00:37:13,191
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

617
00:37:13,251 --> 00:37:16,661
- Young napa cabbage and spinach.
- Okay.

618
00:37:18,431 --> 00:37:19,861
(Young Napa Cabbage)

619
00:37:20,831 --> 00:37:22,161
But, ma'am...

620
00:37:22,501 --> 00:37:24,331
I heard from people
around the neighborhood...

621
00:37:25,071 --> 00:37:27,971
that you've matchmade
quite a few couples.

622
00:37:29,071 --> 00:37:33,911
- Why? Marrying off your son?
- Yes. If there's a good match,

623
00:37:34,041 --> 00:37:35,381
we'd like an introduction.

624
00:37:36,081 --> 00:37:37,751
Well, there is a good prospect.

625
00:37:38,111 --> 00:37:40,611
She went to med school,
worked for a big company,

626
00:37:40,681 --> 00:37:42,251
and now runs her own business.

627
00:37:42,551 --> 00:37:45,221
She's so smart and sharp,
there's nothing she doesn't know.

628
00:37:45,291 --> 00:37:46,851
Oh my, who is it?

629
00:37:47,091 --> 00:37:50,361
Dr. Gong's daughter, Gong Ju Ah.

630
00:37:55,131 --> 00:37:56,161
Oh, I thought you meant
someone else.

631
00:37:56,361 --> 00:37:59,401
What, why? Your families are
on good terms these days.

632
00:38:00,171 --> 00:38:03,071
Oh, is it because you don't like
the idea of being double in-laws?

633
00:38:04,001 --> 00:38:05,671
That's part of it, yes.

634
00:38:07,611 --> 00:38:10,741
Still, it's hard to find
a young woman like her.

635
00:38:11,381 --> 00:38:12,581
In that case, ma'am,

636
00:38:14,051 --> 00:38:17,891
please try to set that young lady up
with someone else.

637
00:38:18,321 --> 00:38:19,321
Excuse me?

638
00:38:20,051 --> 00:38:22,521
Hope business is good. Goodbye.

639
00:38:23,891 --> 00:38:26,931
Absolutely not. That brat.
No way, that's not happening.

640
00:38:28,231 --> 00:38:32,301
I was patrolling the market today.
Why are there so many vacant shops?

641
00:38:32,971 --> 00:38:34,071
Tell me about it.

642
00:38:34,741 --> 00:38:36,841
I heard the sock shop is up
for sale too.

643
00:38:37,341 --> 00:38:39,611
If they start closing one by one,

644
00:38:39,671 --> 00:38:42,681
the other stores
will lose momentum quickly.

645
00:38:42,681 --> 00:38:44,181
Man, this is worrisome.

646
00:38:44,651 --> 00:38:45,651
Exactly.

647
00:38:46,111 --> 00:38:47,881
Hey, you can get anything delivered
to your door...

648
00:38:47,951 --> 00:38:48,951
with a click on your phone.

649
00:38:49,321 --> 00:38:50,421
Who's going to go
through the trouble...

650
00:38:50,481 --> 00:38:51,491
of coming to the market to shop?

651
00:38:52,251 --> 00:38:54,561
That's why we need something
that makes people willing...

652
00:38:54,621 --> 00:38:59,491
to put up with the inconvenience
and come to the market, you know?

653
00:39:00,261 --> 00:39:01,261
Like a night market.

654
00:39:01,961 --> 00:39:03,201
But,

655
00:39:03,501 --> 00:39:06,171
there's a limit to what events
like a night market can do.

656
00:39:06,431 --> 00:39:09,001
Hey, to get through
the nomination screening,

657
00:39:09,071 --> 00:39:11,371
you have to submit that
legislative activity plan, right?

658
00:39:11,771 --> 00:39:14,481
In it, the revitalization
of our market...

659
00:39:14,741 --> 00:39:17,041
you push that
as your main campaign promise.

660
00:39:17,041 --> 00:39:18,081
What do you think?

661
00:39:18,181 --> 00:39:19,981
Revitalizing Onjeong Market?

662
00:39:21,081 --> 00:39:22,081
Sounds good.

663
00:39:22,651 --> 00:39:24,691
I'll talk to Councilor Hwang
when I see him.

664
00:39:24,891 --> 00:39:27,991
Hey, you went for a round of golf
with him,

665
00:39:27,991 --> 00:39:29,391
and now you're best buddies
or something?

666
00:39:29,861 --> 00:39:32,031
Well, not exactly best friends.
More like...

667
00:39:32,091 --> 00:39:33,891
a big brother,
little brother kind of thing.

668
00:39:34,391 --> 00:39:36,731
Gosh, don't count your chickens
before they hatch.

669
00:39:36,801 --> 00:39:39,331
- Gosh.
- He even called me "brother."

670
00:39:40,171 --> 00:39:41,201
I'm so stiff.

671
00:39:45,671 --> 00:39:47,311
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

672
00:39:47,371 --> 00:39:50,811
- Two more servings of ribs, please.
- Oh, you're here.

673
00:39:51,681 --> 00:39:54,311
You both worked hard today.

674
00:39:55,251 --> 00:39:57,681
Well, I'll be leaving first.
I have to go pick up my sister.

675
00:39:57,751 --> 00:39:58,751
Hey.

676
00:39:59,391 --> 00:40:00,521
You know the drill, right?

677
00:40:01,321 --> 00:40:02,591
Don't walk around with earphones in.

678
00:40:02,861 --> 00:40:05,831
Look ahead, and be aware
of your surroundings. Got it?

679
00:40:06,191 --> 00:40:08,161
Yes. I will follow your command.

680
00:40:09,661 --> 00:40:11,401
- See you at home.
- Okay.

681
00:40:11,471 --> 00:40:13,271
- Hey, be really careful. Right.
- Yes, I will.

682
00:40:15,041 --> 00:40:16,771
- All done.
- Okay, let's go.

683
00:40:22,081 --> 00:40:25,281
Woo Jae, sorry for the late reply.

684
00:40:25,511 --> 00:40:28,621
My first day at work was insane.

685
00:40:28,981 --> 00:40:31,651
I'm just now heading home
on the bus.

686
00:40:31,891 --> 00:40:33,091
Getting off work this late?

687
00:40:39,261 --> 00:40:43,261
The saturation in these photos
seems a bit low overall.

688
00:40:43,431 --> 00:40:44,501
Should I do some color correction?

689
00:40:45,071 --> 00:40:48,741
Oh, seriously? You should've told me
before I started editing.

690
00:40:49,101 --> 00:40:53,471
Well, they looked fine earlier,
but now they just look so dull.

691
00:40:54,271 --> 00:40:57,681
Gosh, I seriously want to smack you.

692
00:40:58,311 --> 00:41:01,151
I'm hungry. Go put some
water in that instant ramyeon...

693
00:41:01,221 --> 00:41:02,251
and bring it to me.

694
00:41:03,721 --> 00:41:05,451
Your left arm is
perfectly fine, you know.

695
00:41:05,751 --> 00:41:07,721
Hey, I've been using
my left arm all day.

696
00:41:07,721 --> 00:41:09,661
It's not doing so great either.

697
00:41:10,021 --> 00:41:12,331
- It hurts...
- Oh, seriously.

698
00:41:15,631 --> 00:41:17,731
You should feed me.

699
00:41:18,001 --> 00:41:20,431
It's hard to use chopsticks
with my left hand.

700
00:41:21,301 --> 00:41:22,941
Are you kidding me right now?

701
00:41:23,271 --> 00:41:26,741
And whose fault is it
that I'm like this?

702
00:41:26,811 --> 00:41:28,481
If you have any conscience,
the least you could do...

703
00:41:28,541 --> 00:41:31,311
- take some responsibility...
- Fine, eat. Eat up.

704
00:41:31,581 --> 00:41:32,751
Here. Eat.

705
00:41:36,751 --> 00:41:39,291
- Gosh. Hey.
- Very nice.

706
00:41:39,551 --> 00:41:41,821
Slurping like that
is such bad manners.

707
00:41:41,891 --> 00:41:46,031
- Who cares? We're not dating.
- Gosh.

708
00:41:47,091 --> 00:41:48,101
What?

709
00:41:48,231 --> 00:41:51,161
Answer my phone
and hold it to my ear.

710
00:41:58,541 --> 00:41:59,711
Unbelievable.

711
00:42:01,281 --> 00:42:02,611
(Mother)

712
00:42:07,911 --> 00:42:12,121
- Hello, Mother. What's up?
- Hyun Bin, this Saturday,

713
00:42:12,191 --> 00:42:15,361
- come to a matchmaking agency.
- What?

714
00:42:15,561 --> 00:42:17,321
Just sign up.

715
00:42:17,661 --> 00:42:19,491
Then the manager will
find a good match...

716
00:42:21,701 --> 00:42:23,101
Why not? You should sign up.

717
00:42:23,561 --> 00:42:25,731
You never know. You might
meet the love of your life.

718
00:42:25,801 --> 00:42:28,601
Oh, really?
Then I guess I should sign up.

719
00:42:29,101 --> 00:42:30,101
Gosh.

720
00:42:32,141 --> 00:42:35,311
- Hey, Woo Jae. Been well?
- Oh, yes.

721
00:42:35,911 --> 00:42:37,741
Hey, what are you doing?
Aren't you leaving?

722
00:42:37,811 --> 00:42:40,011
Oh, I'm not finished with work yet.
Just wait one minute.

723
00:42:40,081 --> 00:42:42,121
Come on, who knows
when you'll be done.

724
00:42:42,121 --> 00:42:43,321
I'll take her home.

725
00:42:43,421 --> 00:42:45,491
No, thank you.

726
00:42:45,821 --> 00:42:48,291
- That'd be great, thank you.
- Sure.

727
00:42:48,361 --> 00:42:49,721
Hey! Gong Woo Jae!

728
00:42:51,931 --> 00:42:56,531
Stop screaming so much, will you?
Go and make me a cup of coffee.

729
00:42:57,301 --> 00:42:58,301
Hey!

730
00:43:07,141 --> 00:43:09,781
The next stop is
Onjeong Intersection.

731
00:43:10,241 --> 00:43:12,811
The stop after that
is Cheongri Villa.

732
00:43:23,791 --> 00:43:25,331
Yes, I'm the youngest on the team.

733
00:43:25,961 --> 00:43:28,031
Eun Bin, what are you doing?
Hurry and get off.

734
00:43:28,901 --> 00:43:32,301
What? Oh, sir. I'm getting off too.

735
00:43:37,001 --> 00:43:38,341
Oh my.

736
00:43:44,641 --> 00:43:46,881
That was a close call.

737
00:43:47,811 --> 00:43:49,821
You were dead to the world.

738
00:43:51,751 --> 00:43:53,891
Wait, Woo Jae?
What are you doing here?

739
00:43:53,951 --> 00:43:55,221
Were you waiting here for me?

740
00:43:56,121 --> 00:43:58,591
No, I was just passing by
and saw you.

741
00:43:59,461 --> 00:44:00,691
I was on my way home from work,

742
00:44:00,691 --> 00:44:03,761
and I saw you sleeping with
your mouth hanging open.

743
00:44:03,831 --> 00:44:05,901
I spotted you right away.

744
00:44:06,701 --> 00:44:08,801
I got lucky. If it weren't for you,

745
00:44:08,871 --> 00:44:11,101
I would've ended up
at the last stop.

746
00:44:13,771 --> 00:44:15,581
I passed the interview...

747
00:44:15,641 --> 00:44:17,181
and they put me to work on the spot.

748
00:44:17,281 --> 00:44:20,211
I felt like I was working
for a moving company.

749
00:44:20,281 --> 00:44:23,381
I'm not kidding,
I must've carried 100 outfits today.

750
00:44:23,921 --> 00:44:24,921
That many?

751
00:44:24,991 --> 00:44:27,621
Yes, the actor
I'm assigned to is super picky,

752
00:44:27,721 --> 00:44:29,321
so apparently we have to
pack tons of extra clothes.

753
00:44:29,421 --> 00:44:31,531
Anyway, after going around
to all the sponsors,

754
00:44:31,861 --> 00:44:34,461
picking up all the outfits,
loading them into the car,

755
00:44:34,531 --> 00:44:35,661
and getting to the set,

756
00:44:35,731 --> 00:44:37,661
I have to haul them
to the dressing room,

757
00:44:37,731 --> 00:44:39,601
then set them all up
on hangers, and...

758
00:44:42,571 --> 00:44:45,641
What? Do I have
something on my face?

759
00:44:46,041 --> 00:44:47,041
No.

760
00:44:47,341 --> 00:44:49,881
You say it was hard,
but you look happy.

761
00:44:50,981 --> 00:44:54,011
Yes. I'm exhausted,
but I feel weirdly accomplished.

762
00:44:54,551 --> 00:44:57,581
It's like I'm finally
a useful person for the first time.

763
00:44:59,191 --> 00:45:00,421
Eun Bin. Woo Jae.

764
00:45:00,791 --> 00:45:04,291
- Min Ji Hu, out of your academy?
- Yes.

765
00:45:05,061 --> 00:45:06,061
But why are you two together?

766
00:45:06,361 --> 00:45:09,661
Woo Jae was on his
way home from work,

767
00:45:09,731 --> 00:45:12,971
and he happened to spot
me sleeping on the bus.

768
00:45:13,031 --> 00:45:15,701
He woke me up, so I'm
on my way home safe and sound.

769
00:45:17,541 --> 00:45:20,941
But why are you taking her home?
It's not like you're dating.

770
00:45:21,311 --> 00:45:24,081
We're not dating,

771
00:45:25,181 --> 00:45:27,911
but we're in-laws.
Right, because we're in-laws.

772
00:45:30,521 --> 00:45:34,021
Now that Ji Hu's here, I'm going
to go. Go on. Head inside.

773
00:45:34,651 --> 00:45:37,591
- See you around, then.
- Sure.

774
00:45:40,131 --> 00:45:41,131
Hey, Min Ji Hu.

775
00:45:41,531 --> 00:45:43,201
I told you not to
acknowledge me in public.

776
00:45:43,261 --> 00:45:44,731
Don't make Woo Jae uncomfortable.

777
00:45:44,801 --> 00:45:47,131
Why would you ask that?
Get over here.

778
00:45:59,181 --> 00:46:00,181
Dolphin, you asleep?

779
00:46:00,551 --> 00:46:01,651
Yes, I am.

780
00:46:02,381 --> 00:46:04,621
Come on, you're kidding, right?
Why are you sleeping already?

781
00:46:05,121 --> 00:46:07,091
Let's have some wine
and watch a movie.

782
00:46:07,651 --> 00:46:12,361
I need to rest up, Tamin.
From now on, I'm going to bed early.

783
00:46:14,291 --> 00:46:17,001
Oh, right, right. Sorry,
my bad. Go on and sleep.

784
00:46:24,141 --> 00:46:25,811
(We are with you
to the end of your journey)

785
00:46:33,911 --> 00:46:34,921
(We are with you
to the end of your journey)

786
00:46:36,151 --> 00:46:37,181
(Together,
finding hope at the wait's end)

787
00:46:37,251 --> 00:46:38,251
(Infertility,
Personalized Treatment)

788
00:46:38,321 --> 00:46:39,321
(We offer personalized treatment)

789
00:46:51,431 --> 00:46:55,341
Father. I had a consultation
at a matchmaking agency today.

790
00:46:55,941 --> 00:46:57,271
A matchmaking agency?

791
00:46:57,941 --> 00:46:59,241
You mean a matchmaking service?

792
00:46:59,511 --> 00:47:03,811
Yes. But Hyun Bin is
not being cooperative at all.

793
00:47:04,511 --> 00:47:05,651
Just push ahead with it.

794
00:47:06,311 --> 00:47:10,321
Yes, I'll find a way to convince
Hyun Bin and get it done.

795
00:47:10,581 --> 00:47:12,421
Good. I'm counting on you, Se Ri.

796
00:47:18,761 --> 00:47:19,761
Father.

797
00:47:20,061 --> 00:47:23,461
- Yes?
- What happened to your skin?

798
00:47:23,961 --> 00:47:28,501
- Oh, it's nothing.
- What do you mean, it's nothing?

799
00:47:28,771 --> 00:47:31,171
You have all these red spots
on your skin.

800
00:47:31,271 --> 00:47:34,141
You get all sorts of things
when you get old.

801
00:47:35,111 --> 00:47:36,111
You can go now.

802
00:47:40,311 --> 00:47:43,181
Yes, I understand. Then I'll see
you tomorrow, Councilor Hwang.

803
00:47:43,451 --> 00:47:44,451
Okay.

804
00:47:46,391 --> 00:47:49,191
Honey, did Councilor Hwang
ask to meet?

805
00:47:49,721 --> 00:47:52,631
Well, there's a meeting
with media executives,

806
00:47:53,091 --> 00:47:54,391
and he said he wants
to bring me along.

807
00:47:55,031 --> 00:47:56,161
Really?

808
00:47:57,061 --> 00:47:59,671
Honey, we must prepare for
the nomination review properly...

809
00:47:59,671 --> 00:48:01,031
so we don't disappoint him.

810
00:48:01,201 --> 00:48:03,441
You're right, Se Ri.
Thanks for your help.

811
00:48:04,741 --> 00:48:06,811
Oh, right. By the way, honey...

812
00:48:07,341 --> 00:48:08,811
On Father's skin,

813
00:48:09,211 --> 00:48:11,311
I noticed some red
spots breaking out.

814
00:48:11,611 --> 00:48:12,881
I saw that too.

815
00:48:13,311 --> 00:48:15,221
It looks like
the beginning of psoriasis.

816
00:48:15,681 --> 00:48:18,851
His immune system
must be really weak.

817
00:48:19,491 --> 00:48:22,221
We should take him to the hospital
and get him checked out.

818
00:48:22,421 --> 00:48:24,021
Yes, we should.

819
00:48:36,301 --> 00:48:37,941
Hey, where's Dong Suk?

820
00:48:38,471 --> 00:48:41,571
She's sleeping. She seems exhausted.

821
00:48:41,881 --> 00:48:45,951
She has every reason to be.
What about Father?

822
00:48:46,251 --> 00:48:48,481
Oh, he's in his room. But...

823
00:48:49,021 --> 00:48:52,021
he hasn't looked well
since this afternoon.

824
00:48:52,321 --> 00:48:54,491
Since his memory isn't
coming back quickly,

825
00:48:54,791 --> 00:48:56,921
I think he's getting anxious.

826
00:48:59,931 --> 00:49:01,591
- Father.
- Father.

827
00:49:02,061 --> 00:49:03,831
Have some fruit.

828
00:49:04,461 --> 00:49:06,071
- Oh, thanks.
- You're welcome.

829
00:49:08,001 --> 00:49:10,401
What? What's wrong, Seong Mi?
Are you not feeling well?

830
00:49:11,601 --> 00:49:14,511
No, I just feel a bit nauseous.

831
00:49:14,771 --> 00:49:17,581
Is it because of
the radiation therapy you had today?

832
00:49:17,781 --> 00:49:21,311
Gosh, no.
Today was only the first day.

833
00:49:22,251 --> 00:49:23,421
Father.

834
00:49:24,151 --> 00:49:25,691
Are you very tired today?

835
00:49:26,151 --> 00:49:27,151
No.

836
00:49:27,751 --> 00:49:30,321
Why? Are you upset?

837
00:49:31,321 --> 00:49:32,661
No.

838
00:49:38,061 --> 00:49:40,231
- Have some of this.
- Yes, Officer Jeong.

839
00:49:41,071 --> 00:49:42,071
What?

840
00:49:43,471 --> 00:49:44,671
What do you mean,
an additional crime?

841
00:49:45,341 --> 00:49:47,571
- What?
- What?

842
00:49:48,541 --> 00:49:49,541
Yes.

843
00:49:50,141 --> 00:49:53,311
Yes, I understand.
I'll be careful. Okay.

844
00:49:53,881 --> 00:49:55,421
What is it, Dae Han?

845
00:49:56,881 --> 00:49:57,981
Well...

846
00:49:58,591 --> 00:49:59,751
Hold on.

847
00:50:00,151 --> 00:50:03,491
- What? What is it?
- Just a second.

848
00:50:04,591 --> 00:50:05,831
They got a tip that Jo Mi Hyang...

849
00:50:06,831 --> 00:50:10,331
bought a hammer
at a hardware store in the market,

850
00:50:10,331 --> 00:50:12,131
so they checked the CCTV.

851
00:50:13,871 --> 00:50:15,101
And she was seen holding it...

852
00:50:16,101 --> 00:50:17,601
in front of Mom's pharmacy.

853
00:50:18,271 --> 00:50:19,841
- What?
- What?

854
00:50:21,341 --> 00:50:22,381
What?

855
00:50:35,421 --> 00:50:37,391
I said I'd drop you
off at your house,

856
00:50:37,461 --> 00:50:39,661
so why'd you make me
drive so far past it?

857
00:50:39,791 --> 00:50:41,661
You're the one who said my family...

858
00:50:41,661 --> 00:50:43,101
would get the wrong idea
and start gossiping.

859
00:50:43,431 --> 00:50:44,861
You really hold a grudge.

860
00:50:46,071 --> 00:50:47,201
I'm tired.

861
00:50:48,231 --> 00:50:49,901
I'm tired too.

862
00:50:50,671 --> 00:50:52,741
You made me do all the work.
What did you even do?

863
00:50:52,841 --> 00:50:56,381
What did I do? I saved your life.

864
00:50:58,311 --> 00:50:59,451
Just go.

865
00:51:12,261 --> 00:51:13,431
Gosh.

866
00:51:19,671 --> 00:51:21,471
Ju Ah, behind you!

867
00:51:25,041 --> 00:51:26,241
Let go of me.

868
00:51:32,611 --> 00:51:34,281
Ju Ah!

869
00:51:40,591 --> 00:51:42,421
Ju Ah.

870
00:51:43,391 --> 00:51:45,891
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

871
00:51:48,801 --> 00:51:49,861
It's okay.

872
00:51:50,501 --> 00:51:51,561
It's okay.

873
00:51:55,901 --> 00:51:58,671
Father, please. We'll handle this.

874
00:51:58,741 --> 00:52:02,081
- Father.
- See? What did I tell you?

875
00:52:02,311 --> 00:52:04,811
I told you to use me
as bait to catch her.

876
00:52:05,041 --> 00:52:06,781
Father, calm down.

877
00:52:06,851 --> 00:52:09,881
How can I calm down?
Ju Ah could've been hurt.

878
00:52:09,951 --> 00:52:11,651
And so could your mother.

879
00:52:11,921 --> 00:52:14,151
There were cops posted all around
the hospital and our house,

880
00:52:14,221 --> 00:52:15,221
and you couldn't catch her?

881
00:52:16,161 --> 00:52:18,591
She's been on the run for 30 years.

882
00:52:18,691 --> 00:52:21,591
She's an expert at dodging the cops.

883
00:52:21,691 --> 00:52:24,361
Even so, how are you
going to lure her in, Father?

884
00:52:24,431 --> 00:52:28,331
She's after me.
I'm Jo Mi Hyang's target.

885
00:52:28,741 --> 00:52:30,501
What's this?

886
00:52:30,771 --> 00:52:32,271
It's a letter from Jo Mi Hyang.

887
00:52:32,571 --> 00:52:33,571
What?

888
00:52:36,681 --> 00:52:40,181
She just wants me
by her side again, like before,

889
00:52:40,181 --> 00:52:42,081
so it won't be dangerous.

890
00:52:42,481 --> 00:52:44,851
Sir, your safety is on the line.

891
00:52:45,421 --> 00:52:47,851
Let me discuss this
with our investigation team first.

892
00:52:48,321 --> 00:52:51,721
My family lived
without a father for 30 years.

893
00:52:52,091 --> 00:52:56,661
I can't let them get hurt anymore.
I have to catch Jo Mi Hyang myself.

894
00:52:57,401 --> 00:53:00,671
- Father, I know, but...
- We have to catch her.

895
00:53:01,031 --> 00:53:02,441
Good grief.

896
00:53:02,841 --> 00:53:05,841
(Taehan)

897
00:53:06,171 --> 00:53:08,371
Our Executive Director Hwangbo.

898
00:53:08,641 --> 00:53:10,441
The space that the fashion
division used to occupy...

899
00:53:10,881 --> 00:53:12,211
Should we move
another department in?

900
00:53:12,611 --> 00:53:13,611
Exactly.

901
00:53:13,681 --> 00:53:15,581
(Taehan Group)

902
00:53:15,651 --> 00:53:18,551
You two are perfectly in sync.

903
00:53:19,251 --> 00:53:20,891
What's the status of the rebranding?

904
00:53:21,391 --> 00:53:24,521
We've completed the Group's image
analysis and research.

905
00:53:25,121 --> 00:53:29,231
- And the results?
- Overall, the feedback is negative.

906
00:53:29,531 --> 00:53:30,531
What?

907
00:53:30,661 --> 00:53:34,471
Old-fashioned, conservative,
and slow to adapt to changing times.

908
00:53:35,741 --> 00:53:39,271
Plus, with the recent shutdown
of the fashion division,

909
00:53:39,341 --> 00:53:44,241
the mass layoffs have significantly
damaged the Group's reputation.

910
00:53:44,611 --> 00:53:48,981
Well, fixing that is your job,
Director Yang.

911
00:53:49,051 --> 00:53:52,991
And that's why I created jobs
for the laid-off employees.

912
00:53:53,821 --> 00:53:57,521
He apparently started
a small design company called Pelliv.

913
00:53:58,121 --> 00:53:59,131
Pelliv?

914
00:53:59,531 --> 00:54:02,701
You're supposed to discuss that
when I'm not here.

915
00:54:03,831 --> 00:54:04,961
I'll do as I please.

916
00:54:05,871 --> 00:54:10,541
- Where?
- In Onjeong, near his family home.

917
00:54:10,871 --> 00:54:13,111
- Onjeong?
- You know Onjeong?

918
00:54:13,911 --> 00:54:16,381
Of course. It's been
my main point of interest lately.

919
00:54:17,741 --> 00:54:19,381
Onjeong? Why?

920
00:54:20,011 --> 00:54:23,281
Anyway, in line with Taehan's
new mission and vision,

921
00:54:23,651 --> 00:54:25,491
let's start by redefining
the Group's story.

922
00:54:28,021 --> 00:54:29,091
Yes.

923
00:54:29,621 --> 00:54:33,591
Just as you ordered, I'll make sure
to scrub your image clean.

924
00:54:33,891 --> 00:54:34,931
Scrub?

925
00:54:37,261 --> 00:54:39,831
You should watch your mouth.

926
00:54:42,741 --> 00:54:43,741
I'm off.

927
00:54:43,801 --> 00:54:46,471
(Taehan Group)

928
00:54:49,311 --> 00:54:50,511
Why Onjeong?

929
00:54:50,841 --> 00:54:51,881
Well...

930
00:54:52,181 --> 00:54:53,981
Taehan's new landmark.

931
00:54:54,811 --> 00:54:56,581
I've picked it out as the site
for our new headquarters.

932
00:55:03,291 --> 00:55:05,991
Director Yang is a talented man
I've had my eye on for some time.

933
00:55:06,891 --> 00:55:08,931
He has what it takes to lead
Onjeong into the future,

934
00:55:09,361 --> 00:55:11,001
so please write plenty of
favorable articles about him.

935
00:55:12,831 --> 00:55:16,101
Since you vouch for him so strongly,
Councilor Hwang,

936
00:55:16,201 --> 00:55:18,471
we'll be sure to support him.

937
00:55:18,911 --> 00:55:22,181
Dr. Yang, let's do
an exclusive interview sometime soon.

938
00:55:23,181 --> 00:55:24,311
An exclusive interview?

939
00:55:24,611 --> 00:55:27,311
Yes. How about for a special on...

940
00:55:27,381 --> 00:55:29,081
distinguished local medical professionals?

941
00:55:29,551 --> 00:55:30,681
That's great.

942
00:55:31,251 --> 00:55:33,851
That's a perfect title for Dr. Yang.

943
00:55:35,461 --> 00:55:36,791
Thank you so much, Councilor Hwang.

944
00:55:37,121 --> 00:55:39,461
Then what can I do for you?

945
00:55:39,861 --> 00:55:42,561
It's nothing much. Dr. Yang,

946
00:55:42,961 --> 00:55:45,431
you just need to deal with
the merchants...

947
00:55:45,431 --> 00:55:47,131
protesting the development
project and smooth things over.

948
00:55:47,771 --> 00:55:48,871
A development project?

949
00:55:50,641 --> 00:55:53,611
My pledge is to get rid
of Onjeong Market...

950
00:55:54,141 --> 00:55:57,311
and build a landmark in its place
to represent Onjeong.

951
00:55:59,411 --> 00:56:01,811
Tear down Onjeong Market?

952
00:56:09,591 --> 00:56:10,591
Right.

953
00:56:24,941 --> 00:56:27,941
How are the preparations for
the new product launch event coming along?

954
00:56:28,241 --> 00:56:30,941
We've been getting more inquiries
about the event than I expected,

955
00:56:31,011 --> 00:56:33,881
so it's been hectic.
I even had to work late yesterday.

956
00:56:34,681 --> 00:56:35,721
Hello.

957
00:56:35,781 --> 00:56:36,781
(3H Acupressure Bed)

958
00:56:36,851 --> 00:56:39,151
You're here early.
Please have a seat over here.

959
00:56:40,321 --> 00:56:44,221
Ma'am, our new customer acquisition rate,
purchase conversion rate,

960
00:56:44,291 --> 00:56:46,891
and customer satisfaction scores
are all trending upward.

961
00:56:47,061 --> 00:56:50,931
Oh, really? I've been working
so hard to follow the advice,

962
00:56:51,001 --> 00:56:53,501
I got from the top
store owners last time,

963
00:56:53,571 --> 00:56:54,931
and I guess it's finally paying off.

964
00:56:55,201 --> 00:56:57,901
Right, you're already doing
a great job,

965
00:56:58,101 --> 00:57:00,871
but try to bring in
more repeat customers.

966
00:57:01,411 --> 00:57:04,581
Okay. Then for the customers
who made a purchase,

967
00:57:04,641 --> 00:57:06,511
I'll focus more on follow-up care.

968
00:57:06,681 --> 00:57:09,621
At this rate, you could be in
the running for a top store award.

969
00:57:10,281 --> 00:57:12,491
Oh, a top store?

970
00:57:16,691 --> 00:57:18,161
(Blood Coagulation Test)

971
00:57:21,861 --> 00:57:24,331
Are the blood test results that bad?

972
00:57:24,901 --> 00:57:27,271
You need to get a bone
marrow test right away.

973
00:57:27,471 --> 00:57:29,201
Bone marrow?

974
00:57:29,541 --> 00:57:30,971
Tell your family,

975
00:57:31,271 --> 00:57:32,571
and get admitted to the hospital
right away.

976
00:57:35,711 --> 00:57:37,781
What illness do I have?

977
00:57:39,181 --> 00:57:41,181
(3H Acupressure Bed)

978
00:57:46,521 --> 00:57:48,291
Father, where are you?

979
00:57:48,851 --> 00:57:50,921
Let's go to the hospital together
on your lunch break.

980
00:57:51,321 --> 00:57:54,191
Forget it. I'll handle it myself.

981
00:57:54,661 --> 00:57:57,931
You just worry about getting
Hyun Bin married off.

982
00:58:00,431 --> 00:58:02,071
Father.

983
00:58:02,601 --> 00:58:03,601
Gosh...

984
00:58:08,981 --> 00:58:11,041
What's the photo for?

985
00:58:12,081 --> 00:58:13,811
Oh, it's for...

986
00:58:14,481 --> 00:58:19,121
- A passport. To renew it.
- A passport? Okay.

987
00:58:21,291 --> 00:58:23,961
All right, just relax. Okay.

988
00:58:25,521 --> 00:58:28,561
Okay, I'm taking the shot.
Relax. Okay.

989
00:58:30,201 --> 00:58:33,531
Wait. You can't smile too
much in a passport photo.

990
00:58:34,471 --> 00:58:36,741
Let's do one more. Okay, one, two.

991
00:58:37,241 --> 00:58:39,341
Straighten your back a little, too.

992
00:58:44,681 --> 00:58:48,151
Hey. Is Ju Ah really okay
to go to work?

993
00:58:48,711 --> 00:58:52,251
She was a bit shaken,
but she's fine. Woo Jae took her,

994
00:58:52,321 --> 00:58:53,951
and she said she got to work safely.

995
00:58:55,661 --> 00:58:58,061
I hope Father's okay.

996
00:58:58,421 --> 00:58:59,961
He won't be in danger, right?

997
00:59:00,291 --> 00:59:04,261
The police said they'll watch him closely,
so don't worry too much.

998
00:59:15,311 --> 00:59:16,841
Father, are you all right?

999
00:59:19,511 --> 00:59:21,211
If you feel like you're in danger,

1000
00:59:21,481 --> 00:59:24,321
just press this button.
I'll be nearby.

1001
00:59:24,551 --> 00:59:25,551
Okay.

1002
00:59:26,391 --> 00:59:29,691
Don't touch it or look around.
Just act normally.

1003
00:59:29,761 --> 00:59:30,761
Right.

1004
00:59:30,921 --> 00:59:32,491
If Jo Mi Hyang appears,
you must drag out...

1005
00:59:32,561 --> 00:59:33,991
the conversation
as long as possible.

1006
00:59:34,061 --> 00:59:35,261
Understood.

1007
00:59:35,861 --> 00:59:38,901
She might get suspicious
if you close the clinic.

1008
00:59:38,961 --> 00:59:41,231
Will you two please
act normally as well?

1009
00:59:41,701 --> 00:59:44,001
Understood.

1010
00:59:44,241 --> 00:59:46,541
I'll join the stakeout team
for on-site support.

1011
00:59:48,141 --> 00:59:51,881
Father, don't you dare
try to handle this alone.

1012
00:59:52,141 --> 00:59:54,551
- Got it?
- I got it.

1013
00:59:55,511 --> 00:59:57,481
Dae Han, you should head out, too.

1014
00:59:58,221 --> 01:00:02,891
- Father.
- Don't worry. I'm your father.

1015
01:00:12,371 --> 01:00:14,401
He's heading toward the river trail.

1016
01:00:32,921 --> 01:00:34,391
All clear.

1017
01:00:50,971 --> 01:00:53,641
- Ma'am, could we have more kimchi?
- Yes.

1018
01:01:25,301 --> 01:01:26,611
No sign of her.

1019
01:01:27,041 --> 01:01:28,541
You don't think
she's onto us, do you?

1020
01:01:30,681 --> 01:01:33,581
Let's not expect her
to show up on day one.

1021
01:01:34,251 --> 01:01:37,221
Mr. Gong, don't answer.

1022
01:01:37,451 --> 01:01:40,391
Now, just walk home casually.

1023
01:01:40,851 --> 01:01:44,021
It's the first day.
Let's pull out before sundown.

1024
01:01:52,801 --> 01:01:53,931
Mun Sik.

1025
01:01:54,901 --> 01:01:56,041
Mi Hyang.

1026
01:02:00,311 --> 01:02:01,511
Mun Sik.

1027
01:02:34,011 --> 01:02:36,741
(Recipe For Love)

1028
01:02:37,081 --> 01:02:38,611
Se Ri, hurry up and get him married.

1029
01:02:38,611 --> 01:02:40,281
And you,
make something of yourself quickly.

1030
01:02:40,851 --> 01:02:43,151
I don't have time.

1031
01:02:43,881 --> 01:02:45,781
What? Time for what?

1032
01:02:46,221 --> 01:02:48,551
Are you proposing to me right now?

1033
01:02:48,551 --> 01:02:49,591
Oh my.

1034
01:02:49,591 --> 01:02:51,261
What? I'll be right there.

1035
01:02:51,691 --> 01:02:53,331
Mr. Gong,
we'll be there in a minute.

1036
01:02:53,331 --> 01:02:54,661
Please buy us some time.

1037
01:02:59,631 --> 01:03:02,131
You're not thinking of changing
your pledge, are you?

1038
01:03:02,841 --> 01:03:04,241
Should I find someone else?

1039
01:03:04,341 --> 01:03:07,041
If I do what he asks,
he'll give me the nomination.

1040
01:03:07,041 --> 01:03:09,481
Hey, then you have to.
Whatever it takes.

1041
01:03:10,805 --> 01:03:12,305
Dramaday.me
